Done. Narrowed 3 overly-broad exception handlers:

- **`list.py`**: `except Exception` → `except (InvalidHandleError, AgrError)` — only expected errors when parsing handles or checking status
- **`remove.py`**: `except Exception` → `except (AgrError, OSError)` — domain errors and filesystem errors during removal
- **`add.py`**: `except Exception` → `except (AgrError, OSError)` in `_maybe_suggest_repo_skills` — network/filesystem failures during best-effort suggestion

Updated the corresponding test mock to use `OSError` instead of `RuntimeError` to match realistic failure modes. All 576 tests pass.
